Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placeInstance(25.10)                                      placeInstance(25.10)

Name
       placeInstance - Places a leaf instance in the core box

Syntax
       placeInstance

       [-help]

       instance_name

       <location>

       [<orientation>]

       [{-fixed | -placed | -softFixed}]

       Places  a  leaf  instance  in the core box.  Instance is snapped to the
       site whose lower left corner is nearest to the location specified.   If
       the location specified is outside of the core box, then the instance is
       snapped  to  site  whose  lower  left corner is nearest to the location
       specified. Instance is not checked for legality-it  can  overlap  other
       boxes,  either  placed  or fixed, and it can be placed within placement
       blockages. If no orientation is specified, or if an illegal orientation
       is specified, placeInstance will orient the instance with  the  default
       orientation  of the site in which the instance is being placed. You can
       check the legality of the placed instance by the checkPlace command.

       Note: If you place a master instance blackbox  to  non-R0  orientation,
       the new non-R0 orientation will be converted to R0 orientation.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each placeInstance parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man placeInstance.

       instance_name
              Specifies the leaf instance name.

       <location>
              Specifies x and y coordinates of new origin.

              * x: Specifies the lower-left x coordinate of  the  instance  on
                the x axis.

              * y:  Specifies  the  lower-left y coordinate of the instance on
                the y axis.

       <orientation>
              Specifies the orientation of the instance. Specify  one  of  the
              following values: R0, R90, R180, R270, MX, MX90, MY, or MY90.

              <Default>: R0

       -fixed | -placed | -softFixed
              Specifies that the cell being placed is in the fixed, placed, or
              softFixed status.

              <Default>: -fixed

Example
              * The  following  command places the instance SH22/I40 with mir-
                rored through Y axis orientation at location 1500.3, 980.3  in
                the  floorplan.  The instance SH22/I40 is fixed by default and
                the placement program will not move this instance later:

                placeInstance SH22/I40 1500.3 980.3 MY

              * The following command places the instance  SH22/I51  with  de-
                fault  R0  orientation at location 398.7, 1480.2 in the floor-
                plan. The instance SH22/I52 has 'placed' status and it can  be
                moved during optimization, clock synthesis, or refinePlace:

                placeInstance SH22/I51 398.7 1480.2 -placed

